A scalar product maps a pair of vectors to a number. In other words, at a point p, it is a map g : Tp(M ) ├Ś Tp(M ) ŌåÆ R. A scalar product should be linear in each argument. Hence g is a (0, 2) tensor at p. We call g a metric tensor. There are a couple of other properties that g should also satisfy:

