1. It is symmetric: g(X, Y ) = g(Y, X) for all X, Y Ōłł Tp(M ) (i.e. gab = gba) 2. It is non-degenerate: g(X, Y ) = 0 for all Y Ōłł Tp(M ) if, and only if, X = 0.

